‘Ego Death’ prints are now available! 
.
Link will be in bio 
(I’ve been waiting for a reason to say that…)

‘Ego Death’ features a central figure in a meditative pose, surrounded by patterns and psychedelic imagery that convey a sense of expansion and transcendence. The image captures the intense and transformative experience of letting go of one's ego and experiencing a profound connection to the universe. 
.
Through its vivid imagery and symbolic themes, "Ego Death" invites the viewer to contemplate the nature of the self and the limitless possibilities of the human experience.
.
More print options (ie tapestries and shirts) will become available in the coming weeks, but I’m still getting the hang of this online vendor thing—and prints are first and foremost. 
.

The Celestial Cephalopod 🦑✨
.
The Great Cosmic Squid was originally supposed to be the centerpiece of an upcoming Affirmation reel(and it still might be)—but I strongly felt he needed to stand is his own, without being confined to a tiny square post. 

Like all my mandalas and DM🍵T entities, I aim to merge the ethereal with the geometric, weaving sacred patterns into an organic form. 

An entity that embodies a harmonious convergence of ancient wisdom and cosmic energies, navigating the boundless expanse of space with grace and purpose—inviting all who see him to contemplate the profound interplay of geometry and the mysteries of the universe.
.

✨New Year Portal is OPEN✨
.
A return to the botanical dimension. 
Hues and color gradients merge and dance to symbolize the transformative energies heralding the new year. 
.
Each petal layer portrays the shifts and opportunities awaiting us, inviting viewers to embrace change, growth, and the beauty of new beginnings within its intricate, kaleidoscopic design.
.
Happy 2024! I’m so glad you’re here. 👽
.
(Please notice the stippling I haven’t used in years 😂)

New print shop, who dis?
.
I’m taking over the selling and shipping of my art prints. As a smaller digital artist, print-to-order online stores are great for wearable merch—but the printshop for “wall art” that comes with that service just isn’t cutting it for me. 
.
In February, I’ll be rolling out limited signed and numbered print runs available in “fine art” (silly term🤷🏽‍♂️) giclee style prints, or high quality digital prints. Exciting!
.
